HEADWORD: Insatiableness
<hw>In*sa"tia*ble*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Greediness of appetite
that can not be satisfied or appeased; insatiability.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The eye of the covetous hath a more particular
<qex>insatiableness</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insatiably</ent>⟦br⟧
